# **Running PHP and Postgres Successfully.**

## PHP

- note : (if PHP not installed on the machine then first do this)

```java
# for opensuse

sudo zypper refresh

sudo zypper install apache2 php

sudo rcapache2 restart

# for ubuntu based distros

sudo apt update

sudo apt install apache2 php libapache2-mod-php sudo service apache2 restart
```

### Step 1

```java
— set permissions using this for making sure that php files gets saved .

sudo chmod -R 0777 /srv/www/htdocs #...(for all os)

sudo chmod -R 0777 /var/www/html # ...(for ubuntu based distros)
```

### Step 2

```java
— start the server.

sudo rcapache2 restart #for opensuse

sudo service apache2 restart #for ubuntu based distros
```

### Step 3

— if error isn’t being shown within the browser

— use `phpinfo()` within code , search for Loaded Configuration File

— config file path will be like :- `/etc/php8.3/apache2/php.ini`

— use `gedit /etc/php8.3/apache2/php.ini` for editing the config file

— Uncomment everything related to error within that file

